<seg id=1> U.S. Open Tennis Entered Third Day </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, September 1, dispatches from foreign news agency - U.S. Open Tennis entered the third day on August 31. Last Champion Sampras, recovered from his left ankle joint injury that lasted for more than one month, attended the game and defeated his opponent easily by 3:0 and entered the second round of men's single. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> American player Sampras, the present No.1 in world tennis ranking, has not showed him off on the play ground since mid July. This time he came back after recovery from his ankle injury with a very good condition, and defeated a South African player easily with the same score of 6:2 of three sets in less than half an hour, and entered the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> No.8 seed, Ukrainian player A. Meideweidef won 6:3, 6:4, 6:0 against his rival and entered the second round. </seg>
<seg id=5> He just took this as a gift to celebrate his 20 years birthday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In women's game, No. 2 seed, Sanches from Spain encountered the challenge of his opponent, N.Tauziat from France. But Sanches won the game finally by 6:2 and 7:6. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> No.5 seed, Date Kimiko from Japan, No.9 seed, M.Fielnandes from America, and the Champion of 1990, Sawatini from Argentina etc got smoothly into the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> In addition, according to latest news, American player Michael Chang defeated his opponent in the second round of man's single by 4:6, 6:2, 6:3, 7:6 and entered the third round. </seg>
</p>
